              @{"  " LINK} details check out the MAgicWB  archive for it's licence.
              @{"  " LINK} In  the process of creating this  archive icons drawn by
              @{"  " LINK} (mostly  unmentioned)  authors from all  over the  Amiga
              @{"  " LINK} scene were used.
              @{"  " LINK} The  distribution and  production of  the icons in  this
              @{"  " LINK} archive  is done with the  official  approval of  Martin 
              @{"  " LINK} Huttenloher.
              @{"  " LINK} All  @{b}graphics@{ub} in this  archive may be freely distributed
              @{"  " LINK} to whoever you wish  and by whatever means that may seem 
              @{"  " LINK} appropiate at the time as long  as no rediculous profits
Introduction  @{"()" LINK Introduction} are made from the distribution of these graphics.
Requirements  @{"()" LINK Requirements} All original  @{b}text@{ub} in  this archive is strictly owned by
Installation  @{"()" LINK Installation} me and  cannot be stolen and used  (without changes) in
Distribution  @{"()" LINK Distribution} other guides  (YES THIS MEANS YOU @{b}Tom Oszczepalski!@{ub}).
The  Credits  @{"()" LINK Credits} The  contents of  this archive  may not be  used to kill
              @{"  " LINK} people in any way. (If you DO kill someone tell me how!) 
              @{"  " LINK} All @{b}risk@{ub} involved in using the contents of  this archive
              @{"  " LINK} is not my  problem. It aint cost  ye anything so  U aint
   June 1995  @{"  " LINK} getting anything out of it!   
@endnode

@node DockBrushes "DockPictures"
@{b}@{" Small Magic  ()" system "run >nil: multiview SmallMagic.Demo"} DockPictures @{ub}
              @{"  " LINK}
              @{"  " LINK}  A new thing on your workbench.. Dockpictures are simply
              @{"  " LINK}  dockbrushes that fit together to  create pictures. This 
              @{"  " LINK}  gives you pictures like those bigguns that  crowd  many
              @{"  " LINK}  workbenches but each button is, in fact, four (or more)
              @{"  " LINK}  separate buttons. (Check out the demopic).
              @{"  " LINK} 
              @{"  " LINK}  
              @{"  " LINK} 
              @{"  " LINK} 
              @{"  " LINK} 
Introduction  @{"()" LINK Introduction}
Requirements  @{"()" LINK Requirements}
Installation  @{"()" LINK Installation}                   
